  "text": "Endoscopic retrograde cholangiopancreatography (ERCP) utilizes endoscopy to evaluate the biliary tract. In spite of ERCP with brushings (including forceps biopsies), ERCP with endoscopy, percutaneous cholangioscopy, and cholangioscopy with spyglass, diagnosing cholangiocarcinoma in patients suspected to have cholangiocarcinoma remains particularly challenging. For example, in 2018, a worldwide study revealed that 8-22% of patients \"turned out\" to have benign disease on microscopic examination of resected specimens [CITATION_1] .",
